This paper deals with the study of planarity and quasiplanarity of graphs, which is a fundamental topic in computational geometry and graph theory. The paper presents results on the relationship between $k$-planarity and $k$-quasiplanarity, which are both important concepts in this area. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
